<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 29 at 1:42PM MDT  by NWS Saltlake</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern
Garfield and northwestern Kane Counties through 215 PM MDT...
At 141 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 15
miles southwest of Hatch, or 24 miles northeast of Zion National
Park, moving northeast at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Alton and Long Valley Junction.
This includes US Route 89 between mile markers 98 and 110.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
